data.text:
Vesta Warren, 63 of Bardo passed away Sunday July 31, 2016 at the Baptist Health in Lexington with her loving family by her side.

Vesta was born Jan. 7, 1953 in Harlan to the late Edmond and Hazel Farmer Davis. She was a homemaker and believed in the Holiness faith.

She is survived by her husband of 48 years, Herman Warren of Bardo; children, Matthew Warren of Cranks, Alice Hickey (David Wilburn) of Grays Knob, Kristie (Brandon) Smith of Wallins, Shannon (Donnie) Middleton of Cranks; grandchildren, Vesta (Charles) Epperson, Allison Warren (Matthew Roark), Trevor Cox, Matessa Cox, Kaitlyn Farmer, Brittany Cox, Donnie, Jessica, Amber, and Cameron Middleton; great grandchildren, Caden and Brooke Epperson, Chrislynn Cox, Alexis and Jacelyn Caldwell; 2 sisters, Nancy Osborne of North Carolina and Laura Vosk of South Carolina; sister in laws, Margie Warren and her son Roy Warren, Reba Stewart, and Kathy Warren; she leaves other relatives and friends to mourn her passing.

Visitation will be 6 â€“ 8 Friday (Aug. 5) at the Anderson-Laws & Jones Funeral Home.

Funeral services will be 1:00 pm Saturday (Aug. 6) in the chapel of the Anderson-Laws & Jones Funeral Home with Rev. Ronnie Brock and Rev. Doug Daniels officiating.

Entombment will be in the Grays Knob Cemetery.

Pallbearers will be Jason Caldwell, Charles Epperson, David Wilburn, Brandon Smith, Leroy Smith, and Donnie Middleton.

Please feel free to leave a memory or photo at www.aljfh.com

Anderson-Laws & Jones Funeral Home is honored to be serving the family of Vesta Warren.
